        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-01T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="335"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d335">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.24/199a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-01T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 1, 1942—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>109. Designation of Iran as eligible for Lend-Lease assistance will be announced
                    publicly by White House May 2.<note n="18" xml:id="d335fn18">For text of
                        announcement, which concerned lend-lease aid to both Iran and Iraq, see
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, May 2, 1942, p.
                        383.</note> Iranian Minister in Washington has been informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
